      "content": "The academic debate often involves a push-pull between structural critique and individual agency. Some scholars argue that cultural narratives or community dynamics are simply reflections of the underlying social structures, meaning the \"behavioral\" explanations are often a way to deflect from systemic failures. Others, however, focus on cultural factors, suggesting that certain community norms or internal dynamics can contribute to higher rates of offending, which is a more nuanced, though often controversial, line of inquiry. Ultimately, the most robust literature tends to integrate both, viewing systemic oppression as the root cause that shapes and exacerbates localized behavioral outcomes.",
